<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<p class="p">In order to classify the chilling requirements in all regions of Iran, along with the consideration of daily winter temperatures (December, January, and February), the raw data were converted to hourly data using the Monteith and Unsworth [
 <xref rid="pone.0218725.ref025" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">25</xref>] method according to the following formula: 
 <disp-formula id="pone.0218725.e001" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0218725.e001.jpg" id="pone.0218725.e001g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M1" class="math">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">Hourly</mi>
     <mspace width="0.25em" class="mspace"/>
     <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">temperature</mi>
     <mo class="mo">=</mo>
     <mfrac class="mfrac">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
       <mi class="mi">T</mi>
       <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">max</mi>
       <mo class="mo">+</mo>
       <mi class="mi">T</mi>
       <mi class="mi">m</mi>
       <mi class="mi">i</mi>
       <mi class="mi">n</mi>
       <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
      </mrow>
      <mn class="mn">2</mn>
     </mfrac>
     <mo class="mo">+</mo>
     <mfrac class="mfrac">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
       <mi class="mi">T</mi>
       <mi class="mi">m</mi>
       <mi class="mi">a</mi>
       <mi class="mi">x</mi>
       <mo class="mo">−</mo>
       <mi class="mi">T</mi>
       <mi class="mi">m</mi>
       <mi class="mi">i</mi>
       <mi class="mi">n</mi>
       <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
      </mrow>
      <mn class="mn">2</mn>
     </mfrac>
     <mo class="mo">×</mo>
     <mi mathvariant="normal" class="mi">sin</mi>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <mi class="mi">r</mi>
     <mi class="mi">a</mi>
     <mi class="mi">d</mi>
     <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     <mi class="mi">a</mi>
     <mi class="mi">n</mi>
     <mspace width="0.25em" class="mspace"/>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">(</mo>
     <mi class="mi">H</mi>
     <mo class="mo">×</mo>
     <mn class="mn">15</mn>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
     <mo class="mo">+</mo>
     <mn class="mn">210</mn>
     <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">)</mo>
    </mrow>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
